  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will assist a total of 600 families in the Tsunami-affected secondary level villages in Nagapattinam District in Tamilnadu and Karaikal region of Puducherry Union Territory. The immediate relief support has resettled the families, but they still lack opportunities to build sustainable livelihoods. The 300 original project families will receive 1,200 goats, 40 bucks, fodder seed/saplings and vegetable seed. An additional 300 families will benefit from &#x201C;passing on the gift.&#x201D;  Project participants will receive trainings on Heifer Cornerstones, self-help group management, improved animal management, gender, kitchen gardening and fodder production.  Veterinary services and support will also be provided. This project will also provide refresher trainings to the self-help members of phase I Tsunami project in Nagapattinam and Karaikal.</narrative>
  </description>
